Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop each @corn on the cob{2} on some #foil{} about the size of an
A4 piece of paper. Season with a @salt{pinch} and a @black pepper{good grind}. Sprinkle
on the @Mexican spice{1.5} (use less if you don't like it hot!) and drizzle over some
@oil{}. Massage in the oil, spices and seasoning, then wrap the corn in the foil.
Place on a #baking tray{} and pop on the top shelf of your oven. Roast for
~{25%minutes}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1} into half moons. Peel and grate
the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Slice the @celery stick{1} widthways
as thinly as you can. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium
heat. When the oil is hot, add the shallot and celery. Cook, stirring frequently until
softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add half the garlic and all the @smoked paprika{1.5} to the pan. Season with a @salt{pinch}
and some @black pepper{}. Cook for another ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1},
the @water{200%ml} and the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Stir well to dissolve the stock
pot. Cook until the sauce has reduced by half, about ~{10%minutes}.

Whilst the sauce simmers, drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #colander{} then set
aside. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all) and zest half the @lime{1}. In a
small #bowl{}, stir the coriander and lime zest into the @sour cream{1}. Season with a
@salt{pinch} and keep to one side. Add the black beans to the tomato sauce and cook
for another ~{5%minutes}.

Mix the remaining @garlic clove{1} in another small bowl with a glug of @oil{} and season
with a @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{}. Put the @flatbread{2} on another lined baking
tray and spoon over the garlic oil. Pop onto the middle shelf of your oven until
golden and crispy, ~{5%minutes}. When done, remove from the oven and slice into
2cm wide strips.

When everything is ready, carefully unwrap the corn and squeeze over some lime juice.
Serve the spiced sweetcorn on top of a bowlful of the black bean stew. Finish with a
dollop of sour cream and some flatbread strips. Enjoy!